Read this article:
https://coolestguidesontheplanet.com/create-a-ssh-private-and-public-key-in-osx-10-11/
Create a Global Credentials to utilise from any where:	// 	
	Click on Credentials
	Click on Jenkins
	Click on “Global Credentials”
	Click on Add Credentials
	Select the “SSH Username and Private Key”
	Create a SSH-Keygen key: https://www.ssh.com/ssh/keygen/
	$ cat ~/.ssh/id_rsa		// copy it
	// Paste under private key

	// Second step in GitHub
	Login to Github
	Go to settings
	Click on SSH and GPG keys
	Click on New SSH Key
	$ cat ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub	// copy it
	Add the title as: <Any-Name>
	Paste the public key
	Finally click on “Add SSH Key”

